FBIS3-52512 "drnes003_r_94008" FBIS-NES-94-003 Document Type:Daily Report 5 Jan 1994 India Joint Exercises Called `Threat' to Positions BK0501033694 Delhi All India Radio Network in English 0245 GMT 5 Jan 94 BK0501033694 Delhi All India Radio Network Language: English Article Type:BFN [Text] The five-week long joint exercise by the special forces of Pakistan and the United States begins today. It is to be conducted on the high mountain range north of Peshawar in the North-West Frontier Province of Pakistan. Special forces are commandos trained in paratrooping skills and swift decisive action behind enemy lines. Defense experts feel that the joint exercises pose a threat to Indian positions on Siachen. The experts also say that the joint naval and military exercises with littoral states in the Indian Ocean have become a means for the perpetuation of U.S. military presence in the region.
